# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
`build-ng-packagr` I think

### Is this a regression?

<!-- Did this behavior use to work in the previous version? -->
Unsure

### Description

Unable to build when an abstract component exists inside a library. The compiler complains that it has no module. If you add it to a module there is a type mismatch because the abstract component cannot be instantiated.

Removing the @Component directive means it can get through the "must be exported by a module" issue. However the template and css can no longer be reused properly by components extending this one.



## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
<pre><code>
@Component({
  selector: 'lib-abstract',
  templateUrl: './abstract.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./abstract.component.css']
})
export abstract class AbstractComponent {}

@NgModule({
  declarations: [ComponentsComponent, AbstractComponent],
  imports: [
  ],
  exports: [ComponentsComponent]
})
export class ComponentsModule { }
</code></pre>

## üî• Exception or Error
<pre><code>
<!-- If the issue is accompanied by an exception or an error, please share it below: -->
<!-- ‚úçÔ∏è-->


------------------------------------------------------------------------------
